350 g Cheese Tortellini
1 unit(s) Crushed Tomatoes with Garlic and Onion
56 mL Cream
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
¾ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
1 tbsp Cream Sauce Spice Blend
7 g Chives
2 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
¼ cup Roasted Pepper Pesto
250 g Mild Italian Sausage, uncased
2 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
¼ tsp Salt*

Add 10 cups water and 1 tbsp salt to a large pot (use same for 4 ppl). Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Meanwhile, core then cut pepper into 1/4-inch slices.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.
Thinly slice chives.

Heat a large oven-proof pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter, then the peppers and sausage.
Cook, breaking up sausage and stirring often until sausage is cooked through, 4-6 min**.

Meanwhile, add tortellini to the boiling water.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 2-3 min.
Reserve 1/3 cup (2/3 cup) pasta water, then drain.

Sprinkle Cream Sauce Blend over peppers and sausage. Cook, stirring constantly, until peppers are coated, 30 sec.
Add crushed tomatoes, garlic, roasted pepper pesto, cream and half the chives. Cook, stirring often, until sauce thickens slightly, 2-3 min.
Remove from heat.
Season with salt and pepper.

Add tortellini and reserved pasta water to the pan with sauce.
Season with salt and pepper, then gently toss to combine. (NOTE: If you do not have an oven-proof pan, transfer mixture to a lightly-oiled, 8x8-inch [9x13-inch] baking dish.)
Sprinkle mozzarella and Parmesan cheese over tortellini.
Bake in the middle of the oven until cheese is golden-brown, 5-6 min.

Allow tortellini to cool for 2-3 min before serving.
Divide tortellini between plates.
Sprinkle remaining chives over top.

If you've opted to add sausage, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter, then sausage and peppers. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up sausage and stirring often, until sausage is cooked through, 4-6 min. **

Si vous avez ajouté la saucisse, chauffer une grande poêle allant au four à feu moyen-élevé. Ajouter 2 c. à soupe (4 c. à soupe) de beurre, puis la saucisse et les poivrons. Saler et poivrer. Cuire de 4 à 6 min, en défaisant la saucisse en morceaux et en remuant souvent, jusqu’à ce qu’elle soit entièrement cuite**.

Parsemer les tortellinis de bacon.